sponding to consumer preferencesthe acquisition of whiskey brands reflects the company’s continued interest in responding to a growing consumer preference for whiskey and other dark liquors over lighter liquors like vodka and rum in june  brownforman also purchased slane castle irish whiskeythe purchase includes three malt distilleries one for each of the newly acquired brands a bottling plant and the company’s headquarters in edinburgh scotlandbrownforman’s whiskeys reported sales growth in  whiskey brand jack daniel’s rose  to  million liter cases in  from  million liter cases in  similarly the company’s woodford reserve bourbon brand increased its sales volume  in  to  liter casesdemand for premiumization according to a report by ibisworld the whiskey and bourbon distilleries industrys growth since  has largely been the result of major premiumization consumers have experienced increasing disposable income since  and as a result many have sought higherpriced whiskey brands whiskey distillers are expected to continue steady growth into  the market research report said us demand the us in particular has experienced explosive growth with the number of distilleries reaching a postprohibition high of  according to house spirits ceo thomas mooney who was speaking at the beverage forum event held in chicago this weekproduct differentiation in the form of premiumization is the main driver of growth for many spirit brands including whiskey he added in particular demand for scotch whisky continues to grow especially in the us which saw roughly  million in exports from the uk according to the scotch whisky association  this content is copyright protected however if you would like to share the information in this article you may use the headline summary and link below brownforman answers consumer demand for premium whiskey with purchase of benriach distillery by mary ellen shoupmary ellen shoup apr brownforman corp has agreed to purchase the benriach distillery company for ap